#12201
Outside the Rodon~
You are now standing in front of a two floor neoclassical building, that
seems to have been made sometime in the twentieth century and closer to its
beginning.  It is well preserved though, stone and wood blending to create
an impression of regality and status, and a number of well placed tall,
narrow windows can shed ample light to the inner areas during the day.  The
entrance to the Rodon - marked as such only by a discreet, finely forged
bronze sign painted in red hanging over it - is attended at all times by
formally dressed men in butler's suits and wide-brimmed hats.  The pavements
are cleaned regularly to preserve the immaculate overall image of the
building, and cars are not allowed to park directly outside it, kept away by
posts and silvery chains.  
~
