#12202
The Reception Area~
First impressions being what they are, the Rodon wastes little time or
space to that effect; first a red strip of thick persian carpet ushering
visitors in towards the inner chambers of the building, while on both sides,
there are two artificial rose gardens, each arranged with great care for
detail and lighting, a reflection of the other but very much different. 
Each of the flowers in the garden's left side are made of metal, each a
different one; bronze and silver, iron and steel, lead and platinum and
copper, they all seem to be in different shades of dark colours, all turning
away instead of turning towards a small sun-like orb made of gold which
casts a pale, steady fluorescent illumination from above.  It is the
impression of sunlight that sends the flowers into an ash shaded,
metallically rigid desolation that this setting brings to mind.  On the
right side, a reflection of the last rose garden exists; but this time only
a series of internal, carefully concealed and expertly placed tiny sources
glow to shed colorful rays into a multitude of crystalline flowers that have
been hand-crafted in even the most miniscule details of their petals,
participating in a joyous celebration of bright, fitting combination of
colours unlike their image across the hallway.  Under the nocturnal
celebration the roses are flourishing into a prosperous bloom of vivid
colouration.  
~
