The Rodon's Main Hall~
Very rare are the times, in all hours of the day or night, that the main
chamber that serves as the Rodon's central hall is anywhere near empty;
there are well-dressed uniformed servants and maids constantly moving about
to offer refreshments, pick up leftover glasses or attend to the various
visitors that frequent the building.  It is hard to not notice the
highly-placed narrow windows that during the day will provide plentiful
light on the inside; each of them is fit with coloured glass that provides
