#12204
A Wide Balcony~
From here, some small part of the city and its harbor can be seen, the
waters stirred only by the occasional ship that comes to deliver a cargo or
is sent out for one; there are a very few smaller boats, sometimes yachts
and private vessels enjoying the reverse view that you are, at this moment. 
The street below, central enough to be frequented at all times of the day
and night, is a living thing.  You can see men and women from high above -
each floor of the Rodon's neoclassic building is taller than modern
architecture seems to want them - and they come from all paths of life; from
the hurried walk of an expensive suit rushing for an appointment, to the
slow stroll of couples out for some shopping, to the uncertain gait of drug
addicts and homeless folks looking for a place to spend the night.  It all
seems to be so far from here.  The balcony sports three long tables and
bamboo armchairs with comfortable pillows to allow for some time to be spent
in leisure and relaxation, and there are soft lights above that can be
dimmed to allow for more private sessions.  
~
