#12205
The ball room of the Rodon~
Perhaps so that no one will sit alone in a corner, the Rodon's ball room
has none; shaped to be full circular, with several white and inobtrusive
lights on its high-ceiling casting plentiful illumination and speakers built
into the wooden walls in strategic positions in order to provide the best
results, there is nothing else in the hall that can stand in the way of
dancers.  The floor to the room is perhaps its most distrinctive feature;
old dark wood oak that will squeek softly when stepped upon, made of long
tiles that have been painted and polished until they are literally
reflecting back the images of things and people above them.  The walls
themselves are much different, and yet they blend with the room as a whole
and are evidence of the degree of attention to the detail that has been put
in; made of stripes of painted wood that together depict the scenery of an
ancient, lively forest, there are eyes hidden among those bushes and
creatures blending in with the green, providing dancers with the illusion
that they are celebrating under an old star-lit sky in the kind of woods
that once were, and never will be again.  
~
