#12206
A conference room~
The way this amphitheatrical room's acoustics are designed, a word spoken
from the raised podium will carry well even to the furthest seats or someone
standing by the door without great need for technological enhancements; but
those do exist, as the eye for detail will notice the long series of small
speakers placed up at somewhat elevated positions on each wall to lend those
who employ them an impression of authority.  Except for the podium itself,
the rest of the hall is less brightly lit as to focus the audience's
attention on to the speakers more than each other.  There are tiny red
lights built into the wide, comfortable corridors between each row of seats
to allow for easy passage, and provisions have for brand-new looking leather
chairs that must have quite pricely only by themselves.  
~
